  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-green">
    <div class="callout-label">TruClarify</div>
    <p>The <a href="/log">Creative Decision Log</a> at truclarify.com/log timestamps your creative process the moment you submit. That timestamp is your evidence of human authorship. It takes 2 minutes and it's free. Fill one out for every track before you release.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>The Five Things Catching Suno Creators Right Now</h2>

  <p>I've looked at this carefully. Here's exactly where the gaps are — and what's actually hurting people.</p>

  <div class="pitfall">
    <div class="pitfall-num">Pitfall 01</div>
    <h3>Skipping the AI disclosure box on your distributor</h3>
    <p>DistroKid, TuneCore, and CD Baby all require you to disclose AI-generated content at upload. This isn't optional. Skipping it — even accidentally — can get your tracks removed from every platform simultaneously, your account suspended, and your accumulated royalties frozen. <strong>Read every disclosure question on your upload form. Every time. Answer honestly. It takes 30 extra seconds.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <div class="pitfall">
    <div class="pitfall-num">Pitfall 02</div>
    <h3>Your artist name is conflicting with someone else on Spotify</h3>
    <p>When two artists have similar names, the algorithm conflates them — streams misattributed, discovery damaged, playlist placements confused. If the other artist has established commercial use or a registered trademark, they can file a dispute and your content gets removed. <strong>Check your artist name before you release anything.</strong> The free check at truclarify.com/creators takes 30 seconds and catches conflicts you'd never find by Googling.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pitfall">
    <div class="pitfall-num">Pitfall 03</div>
    <h3>Not registering with SoundExchange</h3>
    <p>SoundExchange collects digital performance royalties — money earned when your music plays on streaming services, internet radio, and satellite radio. This is entirely separate from the royalties your distributor pays you. If you haven't registered, they're holding your money. The average independent artist who's been releasing for 12+ months has <strong>$200–800 sitting uncollected</strong>. It takes 15 minutes to register at soundexchange.com and it's completely free. Do this before your first track drops.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pitfall">
    <div class="pitfall-num">Pitfall 04</div>
    <h3>PRO registration without understanding the AI disclosure requirement</h3>
    <p>ASCAP and BMI require human authorship for registration. If you wrote original lyrics, made substantial arrangement decisions, or added significant human creative elements — register those elements. Be transparent about AI's role. <strong>Do not register purely AI-generated output and claim full human authorship.</strong> This is a misrepresentation that can result in clawbacks and account termination.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pitfall">
    <div class="pitfall-num">Pitfall 05</div>
    <h3>Cover songs without a mechanical licence</h3>
    <p>If you've used Suno to generate a cover of an existing song — even with completely different production, even with AI vocals — you need a mechanical licence. The underlying composition is still protected. Easy Song Licensing handles it for $15–25. <strong>There is no good reason not to get one.</strong> Releasing without a licence is copyright infringement.</p>
  </div>

